# Monthly crawl of all configured sources (ΦΕΚ, ΥΠΕΝ, ΤΕΕ, ...).
# Runs the 3rd of each month at 03:00 UTC — after the National Printing
# House typically finishes publishing the previous month's issues.
0 3 3 * * python -m crawler.main

# Weekly staleness sweep - flags public KB documents whose last_verified_at
# is missing or older than 6 months, for the super admin's manual review
# queue (GET /admin/stale-documents). Monday 04:00 UTC, after the sweep
# would have run against whatever the monthly crawl last touched.
0 4 * * 1 python -m crawler.staleness

# Weekly company-wide-document staleness check - the narrow exception to the
# sweep above: company-wide uploads (project_id/customer_id both NULL) that
# identify an external source via reference_url get content-hash-compared,
# flagging into the uploading company's OWN review queue (GET
# /companies/me/documents/needs-review), never the super admin's. Monday
# 04:30 UTC, right after the public-KB sweep. See
# crawler/crawler/company_doc_staleness.py.
30 4 * * 1 python -m crawler.company_doc_staleness

# Weekly canary benchmark - 10 fixed chat questions through the real
# pipeline (5 construction, 5 tax/accounting), checking gap=false and
# citations present on the persisted chat_sessions row. Monday 05:00 UTC,
# after the staleness sweep. Alerts (failures only) go to benchmark_alerts
# and a super admin notification - see crawler/crawler/canary_benchmark.py.
0 5 * * 1 python -m crawler.canary_benchmark

# Weekly infra-health snapshot - system-wide pgvector index size (public KB
# + every company's uploads combined), classified against fixed thresholds
# and logged to infra_health_checks every run regardless of level. Monday
# 06:00 UTC, after the canary benchmark. Notifies every super admin at
# warning/critical only - infra monitoring, not billing enforcement. See
# crawler/crawler/infra_health_check.py.
0 6 * * 1 python -m crawler.infra_health_check

# Weekly data retention/deletion sweep (legal-blocking - see
# KNOWN_DECISIONS.md). Hard-deletes chat history + documents (60 days after
# cancellation, or 30 days after an explicit deletion request, which always
# overrides the 60-day window) and, on an explicit request, the account/
# profile data too. Never touches the invoices table. Monday 07:00 UTC,
# after the infra-health check. See crawler/crawler/retention_cleanup.py.
0 7 * * 1 python -m crawler.retention_cleanup
